Yobe State Deputy Governor, Idi Barde Gubana has lost his 16-year-old daughter, Khadija, in a fatal road accident that occurred along the Maiduguri-Kano highway. This is coming a week after he lost his son, Mai Mala Buni Junior, in an accident. Khadija, known as Siyama, becomes the latest victim of the accident to have died after sustaining life-threatening injuries. Hussaini Mai Suleh, Press Secretary to the Deputy Governor, in a statement said until her death, Siyama was a student an SS 2 student at Essence International School, Damaturu, the state capital. According to Suleh, the burial of the late Khadija Idi Barde is scheduled to take place at Mai Funeâ€™s Place, Damagum by 4:00 pm, Thursday 16th June 2022.